<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 26 at 1:03PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northeastern Nash,
northwestern Edgecombe and Halifax Counties through 145 PM EDT...
At 102 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 8 miles southwest of Halifax, extending into
northern Nash county, moving toward the northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Rocky Mount, Roanoke Rapids, Halifax, Scotland Neck, Dortches, Red
Oak, Enfield, Weldon, Whitakers and Glenview.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
